🧠 Part-1: Spring Boot Startup Flow (Internal)

When you run:

@SpringBootApplication
public class BankingApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(BankingApplication.class, args);
    }
}

What happens internally?
Step-1: SpringApplication.run()

Spring Boot:

Creates SpringApplication object

Detects:

Web app / Non-web app

Environment

Classpath dependencies

Loads ApplicationContext

Step-2: Creates Application Context

For Web app →
AnnotationConfigServletWebServerApplicationContext

Inside this:

BeanFactory created

Bean definitions registered

AutoConfigurations loaded

Beans initialized

Step-3: Auto Configuration Triggered

Spring Boot checks:

META-INF/spring/org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfiguration.imports


Loads 100+ AutoConfiguration classes automatically

Examples:

DataSourceAutoConfiguration

HibernateJpaAutoConfiguration

WebMvcAutoConfiguration

JacksonAutoConfiguration

SecurityAutoConfiguration

Step-4: Embedded Server Starts

Tomcat / Jetty / Undertow created

Port bound (default 8080)

DispatcherServlet registered

Step-5: Application Ready

Events fired:

ApplicationStartingEvent

ApplicationEnvironmentPreparedEvent

ApplicationPreparedEvent

ApplicationStartedEvent

ApplicationReadyEvent

🧩 Part-2: What is @SpringBootApplication?

It is a combination of 3 annotations:

@SpringBootConfiguration
@EnableAutoConfiguration
@ComponentScan

1️⃣ @ComponentScan

Scans packages → detects:

@Component

@Service

@Repository

@Controller

@Configuration

Registers them as beans

2️⃣ @EnableAutoConfiguration

Core of Spring Boot magic ✨

Automatically configures:

DB

JPA

Kafka

Redis

Web

Security

Cache

Based on classpath + properties

3️⃣ @SpringBootConfiguration

Special version of @Configuration

Marks main class as Spring Configuration

⚙️ Part-3: How AutoConfiguration Works Internally

Example: DataSource AutoConfig

Spring Boot checks:

Condition-1: Class exists?
@ConditionalOnClass(DataSource.class)

Condition-2: Property exists?
@ConditionalOnProperty("spring.datasource.url")

Condition-3: Bean missing?
@ConditionalOnMissingBean


If all true → creates DataSource bean automatically

🔍 Part-4: Most Important Conditional Annotations
Annotation	Purpose
@ConditionalOnClass	Run if class exists
@ConditionalOnMissingBean	Run if bean NOT present
@ConditionalOnProperty	Run if property set
@ConditionalOnBean	Run if bean exists
@ConditionalOnWebApplication	Only for web apps
@ConditionalOnExpression	SpEL condition
